    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/concurrent.futures.html — Python concurrent.futures documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/concurrent/futures/_base.py, Lib/concurrent/futures/thread.py, Lib/concurrent/futures/process.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: concurrent.futures.Executor.submit — __qualname__=='Executor.submit' (len=15); __module__=='concurrent.futures._base' (len=24); __doc__.__len__()==248; co_argcount==2; co_varnames.__len__()==4. concurrent.futures.Executor.map — __qualname__=='Executor.map' (len=12); __doc__.__len__()==1063; co_argcount==2; co_varnames.__len__()==8. concurrent.futures.Executor.shutdown — __qualname__=='Executor.shutdown' (len=17); __doc__.__len__()==491; co_argcount==2; co_varnames.__len__()==3. concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor.submit — __qualname__=='ThreadPoolExecutor.submit' (len=25); __module__=='concurrent.futures.thread' (len=25); co_argcount==2; co_varnames.__len__()==7. concurrent.futures.ProcessPoolExecutor.submit — __qualname__=='ProcessPoolExecutor.submit' (len=26); __module__=='concurrent.futures.process' (len=26); co_argcount==2; co_varnames.__len__()==6. concurrent.futures.Executor.__enter__ — __qualname__=='Executor.__enter__' (len=18); co_argcount==1. concurrent.futures.Executor.__exit__ — __qualname__=='Executor.__exit__' (len=17); co_argcount==4. All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "concurrent.futures.Executor.submit, map, and shutdown all share __module__=='concurrent.futures._base' (len=24). Executor.submit.__qualname__ (len=15) < Executor.shutdown.__qualname__ (len=17) < Executor.__enter__.__qualname__ (len=18). ThreadPoolExecutor.submit.__qualname__ len==25 ties with ThreadPoolExecutor.__module__ len==25; ProcessPoolExecutor.submit.__qualname__ len==26 ties with ProcessPoolExecutor.__module__ len==26 — a structural coincidence showing pool executor qualname and module lengths are equal. Executor.map has the longest __doc__ in this spec (1063 chars). All verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

